Data Cleaning and Processing

Steps Followed
I. Data Imported to Power BI
II. Transform Data - Data Cleaning and Processing
Now inside the Power Query Editor Tool
Remove Duplicates
Remove Null Values -- View>Column Quality
 Easy way , Sort Column
 Home>Remove Rows>Remove Top Rows

Select Employee_ID > Group By in Ribbon> Count
To understand if there is more than 1 record for same employee id

To remove duplicates
select first column, move to last column, Press Shift -, click last column
now all cols selected>right click >remove duplicates

To check if any row names not proper,
check filter of column, 
click any cell in the column, right click>replace

To check the datatypes of each column
Select all columns, Transform> Detect Data Type

Now mostly all data is clean

